Mean Load Derived from Fluctuating Loads
In general, the load acting upon a linear system can change according to how the system
is used.This happens for example when the reciprocating motion is started, stopped as
compared to constant speed motion, and whether or not work is present during transfer, etc.
Therefore, in order to correctly design the life span under various conditions and uctuating
loads, it is necessary to obtain a mean load and apply it to the life span calculations.
